LogFile.FinalText: Some might say than men and women speak different languages. If a man in a relationship says that he does not want to talk about his problems, the typical woman feels that she is being excluded from his world. If the woman says to him that she does not want to talk about the problems, most men think that she does not need to talk about them. These misunderstandings cause arguments. When serious arguments arise, women and men also react differently. New research shows that many women cry when they are angry. In these situations, frightened men choose to leave, and they may feel helpless. Contrary to the crying woman, the angry man uses harsh words. In spite of these different reactions, most men and women are able to live together peacefully, and we probably cannot live without each other.
